cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about a machine learning approach for image segmentation using a neural network to model the conditional energy of a segmentation given an image. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes efficient algorithms for learning deep neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a random forest classifier, which is a common technique in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of 3-D microscopy data, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
